  "text": "In situ hyridization assays using radiolabeled probes were carried out according to methods previously described for cRNA probes [CITATION_1] . Twenty µm sections were cut from quick frozen brains extracted from (C57BL/6 × DBA/2) F 1 hybrid mice and thaw-mounted on to RNAse-free silanized slides. Oligonucleotides complementary to the 5′ and 3′ ends of the human Fe65 coding sequence were synthesized (5′ probe, 5′-GGC CTC CTC CGC CAA GGT CAA GGT CAC ATT GCG ATT CTG GTC-3′; 3′ probe, 5′-CAA GTT TAG AGT GGT CCA GGG AGA GTC CAT TTA CCA AGC AGC G-3′; Integrated DNA Technologies, IA) and labeled with [CITATION_2] S-ATP using terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase (Promega, WI). Approximately 1.8 × 10 6 d.p.m. of 5′ oligonucleotide or 1.3 × 10 6 d.p.m. of 3′ oligonucleotide (2 pmol/ml) was applied to individual slides in 45 µl of hybridization buffer. Slides were incubated in moist chambers overnight at 30_C, and high stringency post-hybridization washes were carried out at 58_C.",
